<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 14:31:46 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>睡眠的振荡生物学：与痴呆症的联系</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-oscillatory-biology-of-sleep-linkage-to-dementia</link><description>在清醒期间，神经调节剂很大程度上独立运作以支持行为和认知。相比之下，睡眠将他们的活动重新组织成协调的大脑节律。在睡眠期间，主要的神经调节剂——去甲肾上腺素、乙酰胆碱、血清素和多巴胺——表现出约 50 秒周期性的同步波动。这些振荡表现为快速（10 至 30 赫兹）脑电图活动的反复爆发，并且与脑脊液流相耦合。神经调节剂是血管活性剂，可驱动缓慢的血管运动，提供支持类淋巴系统清除代谢废物的机械力。神经调节信号传导的破坏（如精神疾病、心血管疾病、衰老或常用处方药物所见）会损害神经毒性蛋白的清除，包括淀粉样蛋白-β和 tau 蛋白。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-oscillatory-biology-of-sleep-linkage-to-dementia2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 14:31:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-oscillatory-biology-of-sleep-linkage-to-dementia</guid></item><item><title>你可以进行精神上的时间旅行——并增强你的记忆</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/you-can-mentally-time-travel-and-supercharge-your-memories</link><description>你甚至可能在不知不觉中重写你的过去。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/you-can-mentally-time-travel-and-supercharge-your-memories.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 14:16:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/you-can-mentally-time-travel-and-supercharge-your-memories</guid></item><item><title>大脑如何以不同的方式记住创伤：理解创伤记忆</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-the-brain-remembers-trauma-differently-understanding-traumatic-memory</link><description>创伤记忆是一种复杂的心理现象，有些经历永远不会被忘记，但只能以碎片的方式被记住。创伤记忆不像正常记忆那样完整或连贯。即使没有细节，实际事件仍然可以给人留下深刻的印象。创伤是由于极度紧张、恐惧或令人不安的事件造成的，这些事件是我们难以应对或感觉无法控制的。这些经历可能是一次性的，也可能随着时间的推移而重复。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-the-brain-remembers-trauma-differently-understanding-traumatic-memory2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 14:01:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-the-brain-remembers-trauma-differently-understanding-traumatic-memory</guid></item><item><title>人工智能现在的成本比人类工人还要高</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-can-cost-more-than-human-workers-now</link><description>当人工智能实验室提高价格时，人工智能上的巨额支出可能会从弹性转变为负债。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-can-cost-more-than-human-workers-now.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 13:46:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ai-can-cost-more-than-human-workers-now</guid></item><item><title>新的“人工智能科学家”正在进步——但也揭示了他们的根本局限性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-ai-scientists-are-improving-but-reveal-their-fundamental-limits</link><description>许多最令人兴奋的科学发现都涉及高度专业化的知识以及在广泛的事实之间建立联系。科学家必须将深入的分析与广泛的推理策略结合起来。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-ai-scientists-are-improving-but-reveal-their-fundamental-limits3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 13:31:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-ai-scientists-are-improving-but-reveal-their-fundamental-limits</guid></item><item><title>麻省理工学院的工程师根据蛋白质的运动而不仅仅是形状来设计蛋白质</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mit-engineers-design-proteins-by-their-motion-not-just-their-shape</link><description>VibeGen 是一种新的生成式人工智能模型，可设计具有动态振动和运动的蛋白质。该模型由麻省理工学院开发，为动态生物材料和适应性治疗开辟了新的可能性。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/mit-engineers-design-proteins-by-their-motion-not-just-their-shape2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 13:16:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mit-engineers-design-proteins-by-their-motion-not-just-their-shape</guid></item><item><title>靶向来自四个中和表位组的 SFTSV 糖蛋白 Gn 头的人单克隆抗体</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-monoclonal-antibodies-that-target-the-sftsv-glycoprotein-gn-head-from-four-neutralizing-epitope-groups</link><description>王等人。报告称，来自 SFTS 幸存者的 Gn 特异性单克隆抗体表现出广泛而有效的中和作用，其中两种在致死小鼠模型中提供了完全保护。这项工作绘制了 Gn 抗原图谱，并建立了一个深度突变扫描平台，并结合布尼亚病毒抗体发现的结构验证。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/human-monoclonal-antibodies-that-target-the-sftsv-glycoprotein-gn-head-from-four-neutralizing-epitope-groups2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 02:11:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-monoclonal-antibodies-that-target-the-sftsv-glycoprotein-gn-head-from-four-neutralizing-epitope-groups</guid></item><item><title>发现抽象思维的大脑区域</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brain-region-discovered-for-abstract-thought</link><description>一项新的研究将大脑用于成分概括的符号引擎定位在腹侧前运动皮层内。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-region-discovered-for-abstract-thought2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 01:56:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brain-region-discovered-for-abstract-thought</guid></item><item><title>中国实验室培育的心脏类器官可以提供起搏器的替代品</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/chinas-lab-grown-heart-organoid-could-offer-alternative-to-pacemakers</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 01:41:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/chinas-lab-grown-heart-organoid-could-offer-alternative-to-pacemakers</guid></item><item><title>宇宙是一台计算机吗？新兴泛计算</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/is-the-universe-a-computer-emergent-pancomputation</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 01:26:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/is-the-universe-a-computer-emergent-pancomputation</guid></item></channel></rss>